cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CL 

This paper investigates how people integrate social information (average review score and popularity) when making choices on online marketplaces and databases. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, as it focuses on user behavior and preferences. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI), as it analyzes how aggregated social information affects ranking schemes. The paper also touches on cybersecurity (cs.CY) and natural language processing (cs.CL), as it involves analyzing textual data (reviews) and potential personalization of ranking schemes.
